A]Create a Shutdown Shortcut-

1.Right click on desktop.
2.Choose New and then choose shortcut.
3.Type Shutdown -s -f -t 00 in location or given MENU.
4.And then click Next,then type name of shortcut as per your wish.
5.Done.
6.You can also change icon from Properties.

B]create a Restart Shortcut-

1.Right click on desktop.
2.Choose New and then choose shortcut.
3.Type Shutdown -r -f -t 00 in location or given MENU.
4.And then click Next,then type name of shortcut as per your wish.
5.Done.
6.You can also change icon from Properties.

C]Create your personal diary using Notepad-

1.Open Notepad.
2.Type .LOG(IN CAPITAL LETTERS) in body and then save the file.
3.Now every time you open the Notepad it will automatically insert current DATE and TIME before the note.
